    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-08T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/9–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Representative on the Advisory Council for
                        Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-08T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 8, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 9—10:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>317. Department 114, August 30, 7 p.m. and my 302, September 4, 5 p.m.<note
                        n="94" xml:id="d687fn94">Neither printed.</note> According to note dated
                    September 8 from the Holy See the approach to the German Government through
                    Vatican channels by the Pope requesting the release of about 9000 refugees in
                    Northern Italy to be transported to Southern Italy or elsewhere was made by the
                    Nuncio in Berlin (Taylor’s 309)<note n="95" xml:id="d687fn95">Reference is made
                        to a communication of September 8 from Mr. Myron C. Taylor, President
                        Roosevelt’s Personal Representative to Pope Pius XII, conveying information
                        repeated herein.</note> with the result that Germany claimed that the
                    authority for these persons rested with the Italian Socialist Republic. The
                    Vatican further indicated that they had no communication with that body. Full
                    text follows by air.<note n="96" xml:id="d687fn96">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
